description.p:
This application is a divisional application of European patent application no. 10 186 691.1 (the "parent application"), also published under no. EP-A- 2 326 077. The following items corresponding to the originally filed claims of the parent application form part of the content of this description as filed.
1. An imaging apparatus (101) including a display monitor (104) for displaying an image, the imaging apparatus comprising:
a grip portion (203) formed on a right side of the imaging apparatus;
a front leg portion (107) formed on a front side upper part of the imaging apparatus;
a rear leg portion (108) formed on a rear side upper part of the imaging apparatus;
a handle holding portion (109) configured to connect the front leg portion and the rear leg portion;
a pedestal portion (112) which is formed further forward than the handle holding portion and configured to store the display monitor with a display surface (401) of the display monitor face thereto;
a projected portion (113) formed further forward than the pedestal portion; and
a hinge member (301) one part of which is fixed to the display monitor and the other part of which is fixed to the projected portion,
wherein the display monitor is drawn from the pedestal portion to an opposite side to the grip portion by rotating the display monitor in a first direction around a first rotating shaft of the hinge member, and
wherein the display monitor is drawn from the pedestal portion to a side of the grip portion by rotating the display monitor in a second direction which is an opposite direction to the first direction around a first rotating shaft.
2. The imaging apparatus according to item 1, further comprising a lens unit (103), wherein the hinge member is fixed to the projected portion further forward than a leading edge of the lens unit.
3. The imaging apparatus according to item 1, wherein the hinge member is a two-axis hinge capable of rotating the display monitor by the second rotating shaft that forms an angle of 90 degrees with the first rotating shaft, and the display surface of the display monitor passes through a state in which the display surface faces rearward of the imaging apparatus and becomes a state facing downward of the imaging apparatus by rotating the display monitor around the second rotating shaft if the display monitor is drawn from the pedestal portion to the opposite side to the grip portion.
4. The imaging apparatus according to item 3, wherein the hinge member is a two-axis hinge capable of rotating the display monitor by the second rotating shaft orthogonal to the first rotating shaft, and the second rotating shaft is set in a position offset from a center line in a short side direction of the display monitor.
5. The imaging apparatus according to item 4, wherein the second rotating shaft is set in a position offset from the center line in the short side direction of the display monitor such that the center line in the short side direction of the display monitor is located in a position higher than the second rotating shaft if the display monitor is drawn from the pedestal portion to the opposite side to the grip portion, and is rotated around the second rotating shaft so as to turn the display surface to face rearward of the imaging apparatus.
6. The imaging apparatus according to item 1, wherein a position of the first rotating shaft is set such that the first rotating shaft orthogonally intersects the center line of the display monitor in the short side direction in a state where the display monitor is stored in the pedestal portion.

claim.claim-text:
An imaging apparatus (101) including a display monitor (104) for displaying an image, the imaging apparatus comprising:
an external microphone holding portion (114) formed on one side of the imaging apparatus and adapted to hold an external microphone;
a front leg portion (107) formed on a front side upper part of the imaging apparatus;
a rear leg portion (108) formed on a rear side upper part of the imaging apparatus;
a handle holding portion (109) configured to connect the front leg portion and the rear leg portion;
a pedestal portion (112) which is formed further forward than the handle holding portion (109) and configured to store the display monitor with a display surface (401) of the display monitor face thereto;
a projected portion (113) formed further forward than the pedestal portion (112); and
a hinge member (301) one part of which is fixed to the display monitor and the other part of which is fixed to the projected portion (113), wherein the hinge member (301) is a two-axis hinge capable of rotating the display monitor (104) by a first rotating shaft (303) and a second rotating shaft (304) orthogonal to the first rotating shaft (303),
characterized in that
the hinge member (301) enables that the display monitor (104) is drawn from a first state that the display monitor (104) is stored in the pedestal portion (112) to a second state that the display monitor (104) is in a side of the external microphone holding portion (114) by rotating the display monitor (104) in a first direction around the first rotating shaft (303),
in a case where the display monitor (104) is in the second state, the display monitor (104) is drawn around the second rotating shaft (304) to a state in which the display surface faces rearward of the imaging apparatus (101),
in a case where the display monitor is in the second state and the display surface faces rearward of the imaging apparatus (101), the external microphone holding portion (114) is positioned behind the display monitor (104), and the second rotating shaft (304) is set in a position offset from a center line in a short side direction of the display monitor (104) such that the center line in the short side direction of the display monitor (104) is located in a position lower than the second rotating shaft (304).
